Game design Game design Types of games: action, shooter, adventure, role-playing, simulation, strategy, single vs. (massive) multi-player, etc. Typical goals in "general HCI design": reduce error rate, increase speed of task performance, improve retention, user satisfaction... Additional predominant goal in game design: give users "fun" challenges, rewards, fantasy, immersion, surprises, control/dominance, social interaction/bonding Guidelines: Game story Game interface Game mechanics Game play Non-entertainment applications: education, training, following regimens